JOHANNESBURG - The families of 18 schoolchildren killed in a crash between a minibus and coal truck two weeks ago have asked for continued support.A memorial service has been held for the children in Sokhulumi village between Bronkhorstspruit and Verena on the R25. READ: Verena horror crash victims to be laid to restAuthorities used DNA to identify each of the children killed.Some families lost more than one child in the crash which saw the minibus burst into flames, burning its passengers beyond recognition.Another service will be held on Thursday ahead of a mass funeral over the weekend.eNCA